<br>
Hopefully we will pick up a couple more clerics, a chanter, a necro and a few more FD capable classes before the raid. <br>
<br>
Limbino zones in with regrowth on and FDs where he can see the portal and as much of the run to camp as possible.<br>
<br>
If available, a Necro will harm shield themself, and have rune cast on them. If the person is simply FD capable just Rune.<br>
<br>
Tactical control at this point passes to Limbino. He will call For the trainer, if we have one, to zone and create a train north. They will do this by spiraling to thier Left once they zone in and running north on the right hand side of the portal. <br>
This makes use of a known pathing issue in fear. A mobs Normal path is a straight line | . If it aggros something its path is changed into an arc ) with the farthest point of the bow where aggro ended. This path slowly returns to normal as the mob wanders its path, eact time the bow becoming a little less till the path finally returns to normal.<br>
<br>
Limbino then calls for the break groups to zone ( groups 1, 2, and 3). Once you pop in zone stop for a moment, and turn so the portal is on your left, and you are moving parallel to its face when you run. Go down the hill to the camp, and stay close together! If you get aggroed stop and fight DO NOT TRAIN THE CAMP. <br>
<br>
Once at the camp tactical control passes to the Snaake, Stupie, or Jjackel in that order. Stupie taking control if Snaake goes down etc. <br>
<br>
Clerics need to heal early and often, Superior or celstial healing prefered for faster cast times. <br>
<br>
The Druids have 2 critical jobs at this point. First they heal the Chanters so the clerics can focus on the MA / SA. Second is they call the evac. Druids in the break in group will make a hotkey with 2 shouts of Evac, the cast command for thier evac spell, and 2 more shouts of Evac. If the cleric or chanter calls 20m, or 2 melees from the group have gone down that druid will call the evac, and all groups will evac at that point. Break group will return to the portal, rebuff and repeat as many times as needed untill the camp is clear enough for the rest of the raid party to enter.<br>
<br>
<br>
When dealing with Fear the raid is a success or failure based on the break. <br>
<br>
Preraid meeting will be Saturday 8 pm EST in chat, Group leaders, scout, MA, SAs are required to attend, all others are welcome to attend if they like. The point of this meeting will be to review the plan, and clarify anything needed so everyone knows thier part.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25979"target="_blank">Benadan</a><br
